com.sap.cloud.sdk.frameworks.liquibase

Class SchemaPerTenantProvisioner

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sap.cloud.sdk.frameworks.liquibase.SchemaPerTenantProvisioner

  • public class SchemaPerTenantProvisioner
extends Object
    This class provides helper methods with the default implementation of the tenant on-boarding and off-boarding for schema per tenant multi-tenancy. JDBC connection and a path to a liquibase configuration file for a database schema migration need to be passed during initialization.

      • SchemaPerTenantProvisioner

        public SchemaPerTenantProvisioner(Connection connection,
                                  String liquibaseConfigPath)
        Initializes the new instance based on the given JDBC connections and the path to a liquibase configuration file.

        The default prefix for the schema used by this constructor is stored in DEFAULT_SCHEMA_PREFIX.

        Parameters:
        connection - The JDBC connection to the database to be managed.
        liquibaseConfigPath - The path to a liquibase configuration file containing the schema to use.

        Parameters:
        connection - The JDBC connection to the database to be managed.
        liquibaseConfigPath - The path to a liquibase configuration file containing the schema to use.
        schemaPrefix - The prefix to be used for the name of each tenant schema.

    • Method Detail

      • subscribeTenant

        public void subscribeTenant(String tenantId)
                     throws IllegalArgumentException,
                            SQLException,
                            liquibase.exception.LiquibaseException
        This method provides the default implementation for the tenant onboarding for a given tenantId. The method creates a database schema for a tenantId based on a given connection and liquibase configuration. In this default implementation, the name of the schema is equal to tenantId. The tenant id may only contain alphanumerical characters as well as '_' and '-'.
        Parameters:
        tenantId - The id of the tenant to build the schema for.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the constructed schema name contains invalid characters.
        SQLException - If there was a problem during the creation of the schema.
        liquibase.exception.LiquibaseException - If there was a problem while applying the liquibase configuration.

      • unsubscribeTenant

        public void unsubscribeTenant(String tenantId)
                       throws IllegalArgumentException,
                              SQLException
        This method provides the default implementation for the tenant offboarding for a given tenantId. It removes a corresponding database schema and all related tables. The tenant id may only contain alphanumerical characters as well as '_' and '-'.
        Parameters:
        tenantId - The id of the tenant to drop the schema for.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the constructed schema name contains invalid characters.
        SQLException - If there was a problem with the SQL command.
